Where should the custom message appear? Prepend `(1)` or append `(2)` it to the existing one?

```java
String message = "XXX";
List<String> expected = Arrays.asList("a", "b", "c");
List<String> actual = Arrays.asList("a", "d", "c");

Error error = assertThrows(Error.class, () -> assertLinesMatch(expected, actual, message));
List<String> expectedErrorMessageLines = Arrays.asList( //
		message + " ==> " + "expected line #2:`b` doesn't match ==> expected: <a", // (1)
		"b", //
		"c> but was: <a", //
		"d", //
		"c>" + "  ==> "+ message); (2)
assertLinesMatch(expectedErrorMessageLines, Arrays.asList(error.getMessage().split("\\R")));
```
